newsitem.title: USA: CBOT nearby soymeal ends firm on cash talk.
newsitem.headline: CBOT nearby soymeal ends firm on cash talk.

text.p: CBOT nearby soymeal contracts closed higher on talk of strong cash soymeal basis values in South America, traders said.
The posting of no deliveries Wednesday on the August contract also was supportive and the August expired quietly at 1201 CDT at $263.90 per ton, up $0.90.
Reports from a U.S. crop tour, confirming potential poor yield prospects in the eastern portion of the U.S. soybean growing region underpinned the market.
Cash-connected deliveries posted this week on the August pressured soyoil.
The August soyoil contract expired without fanfare at 1201 CDT at 25.10, unchanged.
Soymeal closed $1.20 per ton higher to $0.50 lower, with September up $1.20 at $255.70. Soyoil was 0.07 cent per lb lower to 0.05 higher, with September down 0.03 at 25.12.
Soymeal futures volume was estimated at 21,000 contracts, down from 23,525 Tuesday. Soymeal options volume was estimated at 1,500, down from 2,082 Tuesday.
Soyoil futures volume was estimated at 16,000, up from 14,082 Tuesday. Soyoil options volume was estimated at 1,400, up from 1,088 Tuesday.
